ry after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Sir William FitzAdams was born about 1165, in Charlton Adam, Somerset, England, United Kingdom, his father, Caradog ap Meurig of Penrhos, was 41 and his mother, Maude Matilda Fitz Walter, was 29. He married Alice de Crèvecoeur in 1190, in Somerset, England. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. He died about 1206, in Hereford, Herefordshire, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 43."},"et":{"about 1165–about 1206":"umbes 1165–umbes 1206","1160–1250":"1160–1250","1165–1206":"1165–1206","1163–1247":"1163–1247","1190–Male":"1190–Surnud","1195–1252":"1195–1252","1125–1173":"1125–1173","1137–Female":"1137–Surnud","1190":"1190","1165":"1165","1252":"1252","1163":"1163","1173":"1173","1195":"1195","1250":"1250","1160":"1160","1206":"1206","1137":"1137","1247":"1247","about 1206":"umbes 1206","1125":"1125","about 1165":"umbes 1165","before 1160":"enne 1160","Somerset, England":"Somerset, England","Penrhos, Wales":"Penrhos, Montgomeryshire, Wales, United Kingdom","Hereford, Herefordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Hereford, Herefordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Charlton Adam, Somerset, England, United Kingdom":"Charlton Adam, Somerset, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Europe":"Europe","Charleton Fitz Adam, Somerset, England":"Somerset, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"England"},"fi":{"about 1165–about 1206":"noin 1165–noin 1206","1160–1250":"1160–1250","1165–1206":"1165–1206","1163–1247":"1163–1247","1190–Male":"1190–Kuollut","1195–1252":"1195–1252","1125–1173":"1125–1173","1137–Female":"1137–Kuollut","1190":"1190","1165":"1165","1252":"1252","1163":"1163","1173":"1173","1195":"1195","1250":"1250","1160":"1160","1206":"1206","1137":"1137","1247":"1247","about 1206":"noin 1206","